The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Johannesburg: Cricket South Africa Friday said that the country will be hosting the Champions League Twenty20 from September 10-26, ending speculation on the venue of the multi-million dollar international event. The competition will take place across three venues, two of which will be the home grounds of this years Standard Bank Pro20 finalists. This is a prestigious tournament involving seven of the worlds top cricket nations. It will be another feather in South Africas cap as a host of world-class sports events CSA president Dr Mtutuzeli Nyoka said in a media release. The tournament, hosted in India last year, will feature 12 teams, including three from this years IPL.      
	Umpire honour
    
	Calcutta: International Cricket Council umpire Asoka de Silva was Friday honoured for standing in a century of ODIs, a landmark reached during the series between Australia and Pakistan Down Under. De Silva became only the 12th umpire to reach the milestone.  
	Shooters shine  
	New Delhi: Gagan Narang and P.T. Raghunath set a new meet record in the 10m air rifle team event as Indian shooters dominated proceedings with two gold, one silver and a bronze on the opening day of the Commonwealth Championships here Friday. Anisa Sayyed and Annuraj Singh won the second gold in the 25m pistol team event.  
	Challenge over  
	Belgrade: The Indian challenge ended at the ATP Challenger event here ended with defeats for Somdev Dev Varman and Prakash Amritraj, respectively, in the singles and doubles events.      
	Colombo: Defending champions India Friday lost 0-1 against Turkmenistan to crash out of the AFC Challenge Cup. The Indian under 23 side fell behind to a 23rd minute penalty by Karadanov Mamedaly.        
	Kannur: East Bengal and Lajong FC played out a goalless draw in their pool B encounter in the third EK Nayanar Memorial gold cup tournment Friday.                                                                                                                                                       
